A man was bitten by a python while he was attempting to take a selfie.According to news.sky.com, the incident happened in India&#8217;s northwestern Rajasthan state after forest department officials removed the snake from a school.In a video posted on YouTube, a group of men are seen holding the python and posing for pictures after successfully capturing it.A man moved closer for a selfie and was attacked by the snake, which lunged forward and bit him on the shoulder.The man only suffered minor injuries and the snake was then taken away.-TNA Reporter 